  "texts": [
    "The performance of the LLMs on the MMLU 50, GPQA 49, and DROP 51 benchmarks, collected from the following references 38, 39, 48.",
    "Similarly, other studies 10, 24 discussed that ChatGPT has great potential for nutritional management focusing on non-communicable diseases, but the model might be potentially harmful by providing inaccurate responses, particularly in complex situations.",
    "Another study 22 leveraged ChatGPT-3.5 and ChatGPT-4 to provide nutritional information for eight menus.",
    "Their results indicated that responses had no significant differences compared to nutritionists' recommendations in terms of energy, carbohydrate, and fat contents, but the difference was statistically significant for protein.",
    "The potential of ChatGPT to generate dietary advice for patients with allergic to food allergens were also investigated 27."
  ]
